	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64246634"><p>Johnny can't math because the school teachers, as a group, can't math. People who can math command higher salaries than school teachers in all but the top 20% or so school districts.</p><p>So if Johnny lives in a suburb where the schools budget actually goes to teacher salaries, he might learn to math from someone who can put 2 and 2 together and get 4 more often than not. But if Johnny goes to school in a big city district where that same money gets pissed away on teaching half the kids how they're oppressed and the other half how they're the oppressors, that don't leave much money for paying people who know what they're doing.</p></div>
